Feature: the canonical lead CLAUDE.md primer defines the effectively-empty / no-product-defined repo detection signal so a freshly bootstrapped lead can recognize that no product has been shaped yet

  lead-vglj (P2) — product authority 2026-06-29 (verbatim): "for the lead to
  detect when the repo is effectively empty and start a product discovery
  conversation with the user to start determining the shape of the new system."

  This scenario pins the DETECTION half: the canonical lead primer (rendered into
  every product's lead via shop-templates) must define what "effectively empty"
  observably means, so the router can recognize the no-product-defined state. The
  bootstrap scaffold itself writes canonical-managed files (CLAUDE.md, the typed
  .claude/shop/* files, agent definitions, settings, an empty/initialized beads
  registry, a placeholder shop primer) — those do NOT constitute a product. The
  observable signal is the absence of any PRODUCT-BEARING artifact beyond that
  scaffold: no substantive brief, no PDR, no features/ scenario, no
  product-bearing bead.

  Ties to the existing product-authority discovery gate in the lead primer (which
  governs WHERE the discovery dialogue happens); this scenario adds the empty-repo
  detection signal that the proactive-initiation trigger (sibling scenario, file
  222) fires on.

  SCOPE THINNESS FLAGGED FOR PRODUCT ROUND-TRIP: the exact membership of the
  "product-bearing artifact" set — and whether an empty/initialized-only beads
  registry counts as scaffold vs. product — is the PO's provisional reading of the
  authority's words, pending confirmation when the authority returns.

  AUTHORING ONLY — no BC dispatch. @bc tag is the Architect's to apply at
  assignment time; @lead_integration:templates below is provisional placement
  matching sibling primer-furniture scenarios.

@lead_integration:templates
  @scenario_hash:8d141b60dea4b2f8
  Scenario: the canonical lead primer defines the effectively-empty / no-product-defined detection signal as the absence of any product-bearing artifact beyond the bootstrap scaffold
    Given the "shop-templates" package ships a canonical "CLAUDE.md" primer template for shop type "lead" through its public template-access surface
    When I ask the package for that canonical primer body for shop type "lead"
    Then a non-empty template body is returned
    And the returned body contains a contiguous block defining an effectively-empty / no-product-defined repo state
    And that block names the observable signal as the absence of any product-bearing brief, PDR, "features/" scenario, or product-bearing bead beyond the artifacts the bootstrap scaffold itself writes
    And that block distinguishes the bootstrap scaffold — canonical-managed files, the placeholder shop primer, and the initialized-but-empty beads registry — from product-bearing artifacts so that the scaffold alone counts as effectively empty
